8937 auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(1));
8938 if (!C || !C->isNullValue())
8939 return SDValue();
8940 SDValue Args[] = { LHS.getOperand(0), RHS, LHS.getOperand(2) };
8941 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUBCARRY, SDLoc(N), LHS->getVTList(), Args);
8942 }
8943 return SDValue();
8944}
8945
8946SDValue SITargetLowering::performAddCarrySubCarryCombine(SDNode *N,
8947 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
8948
8949 if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i32)
8950 return SDValue();
8951
8952 auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
8953 if (!C || C->getZExtValue() != 0)
8954 return SDValue();
8955
8956 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
8957 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
8958
8959 // addcarry (add x, y), 0, cc => addcarry x, y, cc
8960 // subcarry (sub x, y), 0, cc => subcarry x, y, cc
8961 unsigned LHSOpc = LHS.getOpcode();
8962 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
8963 if ((LHSOpc == ISD::ADD && Opc == ISD::ADDCARRY) ||
8964 (LHSOpc == ISD::SUB && Opc == ISD::SUBCARRY)) {
8965 SDValue Args[] = { LHS.getOperand(0), LHS.getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2) };
8966 return DAG.getNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), N->getVTList(), Args);
8967 }
8968 return SDValue();
8969}
8970
8971SDValue SITargetLowering::performFAddCombine(SDNode *N,
8972 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
8973 if (DCI.getDAGCombineLevel() < AfterLegalizeDAG)
8974 return SDValue();
8975
8976 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
8977 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
8978
8979 SDLoc SL(N);
8980 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
8981 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
8982
8983 // These should really be instruction patterns, but writing patterns with
8984 // source modiifiers is a pain.
8985
8986 // fadd (fadd (a, a), b) -> mad 2.0, a, b
8987 if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
8988 SDValue A = LHS.getOperand(0);
8989 if (A == LHS.getOperand(1)) {
8990 unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, LHS.getNode());
8991 if (FusedOp != 0) {
8992 const SDValue Two = DAG.getConstantFP(2.0, SL, VT);
8993 return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, Two, RHS);
8994 }
8995 }
8996 }
8997
8998 // fadd (b, fadd (a, a)) -> mad 2.0, a, b
8999 if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
9000 SDValue A = RHS.getOperand(0);
9001 if (A == RHS.getOperand(1)) {
9002 unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, RHS.getNode());
9003 if (FusedOp != 0) {
9004 const SDValue Two = DAG.getConstantFP(2.0, SL, VT);
9005 return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, Two, LHS);
9006 }
9007 }
9008 }
9009
9010 return SDValue();
9011}
9012
9013SDValue SITargetLowering::performFSubCombine(SDNode *N,
9014 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9015 if (DCI.getDAGCombineLevel() < AfterLegalizeDAG)
9016 return SDValue();
9017
9018 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9019 SDLoc SL(N);
9020 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9021 assert(!VT.isVector());
9022
9023 // Try to get the fneg to fold into the source modifier. This undoes generic
9024 // DAG combines and folds them into the mad.
9025 //
9026 // Only do this if we are not trying to support denormals. v_mad_f32 does
9027 // not support denormals ever.
9028 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
9029 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
9030 if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
9031 // (fsub (fadd a, a), c) -> mad 2.0, a, (fneg c)
9032 SDValue A = LHS.getOperand(0);
9033 if (A == LHS.getOperand(1)) {
9034 unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, LHS.getNode());
9035 if (FusedOp != 0){
9036 const SDValue Two = DAG.getConstantFP(2.0, SL, VT);
9037 SDValue NegRHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, SL, VT, RHS);
9038
9039 return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, Two, NegRHS);
9040 }
9041 }
9042 }
9043
9044 if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
9045 // (fsub c, (fadd a, a)) -> mad -2.0, a, c
9046
9047 SDValue A = RHS.getOperand(0);
9048 if (A == RHS.getOperand(1)) {
9049 unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, RHS.getNode());
9050 if (FusedOp != 0){
9051 const SDValue NegTwo = DAG.getConstantFP(-2.0, SL, VT);
9052 return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, NegTwo, LHS);
9053 }
9054 }
9055 }
9056
9057 return SDValue();
9058}
9059
9060SDValue SITargetLowering::performFMACombine(SDNode *N,
9061 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9062 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9063 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9064 SDLoc SL(N);
9065
9066 if (!Subtarget->hasDot2Insts() || VT != MVT::f32)
9067 return SDValue();
9068
9069 // FMA((F32)S0.x, (F32)S1. x, FMA((F32)S0.y, (F32)S1.y, (F32)z)) ->
9070 // FDOT2((V2F16)S0, (V2F16)S1, (F32)z))
9071 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(0);
9072 SDValue Op2 = N->getOperand(1);
9073 SDValue FMA = N->getOperand(2);
9074
9075 if (FMA.getOpcode() != ISD::FMA ||
9076 Op1.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND ||
9077 Op2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND)
9078 return SDValue();
9079
9080 // fdot2_f32_f16 always flushes fp32 denormal operand and output to zero,
9081 // regardless of the denorm mode setting. Therefore, unsafe-fp-math/fp-contract
9082 // is sufficient to allow generaing fdot2.
9083 const TargetOptions &Options = DAG.getTarget().Options;
9084 if (Options.AllowFPOpFusion == FPOpFusion::Fast || Options.UnsafeFPMath ||
9085 (N->getFlags().hasAllowContract() &&
9086 FMA->getFlags().hasAllowContract())) {
9087 Op1 = Op1.getOperand(0);
9088 Op2 = Op2.getOperand(0);
9089 if (Op1.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ||
9090 Op2.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT)
9091 return SDValue();
9092
9093 SDValue Vec1 = Op1.getOperand(0);
9094 SDValue Idx1 = Op1.getOperand(1);
9095 SDValue Vec2 = Op2.getOperand(0);
9096
9097 SDValue FMAOp1 = FMA.getOperand(0);
9098 SDValue FMAOp2 = FMA.getOperand(1);
9099 SDValue FMAAcc = FMA.getOperand(2);
9100
9101 if (FMAOp1.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND ||
9102 FMAOp2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND)
9103 return SDValue();
9104
9105 FMAOp1 = FMAOp1.getOperand(0);
9106 FMAOp2 = FMAOp2.getOperand(0);
9107 if (FMAOp1.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ||
9108 FMAOp2.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT)
9109 return SDValue();
9110
9111 SDValue Vec3 = FMAOp1.getOperand(0);
9112 SDValue Vec4 = FMAOp2.getOperand(0);
9113 SDValue Idx2 = FMAOp1.getOperand(1);
9114
9115 if (Idx1 != Op2.getOperand(1) || Idx2 != FMAOp2.getOperand(1) ||
9116 // Idx1 and Idx2 cannot be the same.
9117 Idx1 == Idx2)
9118 return SDValue();
9119
9120 if (Vec1 == Vec2 || Vec3 == Vec4)
9121 return SDValue();
9122
9123 if (Vec1.getValueType() != MVT::v2f16 || Vec2.getValueType() != MVT::v2f16)
9124 return SDValue();
9125
9126 if ((Vec1 == Vec3 && Vec2 == Vec4) ||
9127 (Vec1 == Vec4 && Vec2 == Vec3)) {
9128 return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FDOT2, SL, MVT::f32, Vec1, Vec2, FMAAcc,
9129 DAG.getTargetConstant(0, SL, MVT::i1));
9130 }
9131 }
9132 return SDValue();
9133}
9134
9135SDValue SITargetLowering::performSetCCCombine(SDNode *N,
9136 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9137 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9138 SDLoc SL(N);
9139
9140 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
9141 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
9142 EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
9143 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->get();
9144
9145 auto CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS);
9146 if (!CRHS) {
9147 CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS);
9148 if (CRHS) {
9149 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
9150 CC = getSetCCSwappedOperands(CC);
9151 }
9152 }
9153
9154 if (CRHS) {
9155 if (VT == MVT::i32 && LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND &&
9156 isBoolSGPR(LHS.getOperand(0))) {
9157 // setcc (sext from i1 cc), -1, ne|sgt|ult) => not cc => xor cc, -1
9158 // setcc (sext from i1 cc), -1, eq|sle|uge) => cc
9159 // setcc (sext from i1 cc), 0, eq|sge|ule) => not cc => xor cc, -1
9160 // setcc (sext from i1 cc), 0, ne|ugt|slt) => cc
9161 if ((CRHS->isAllOnesValue() &&
9162 (CC == ISD::SETNE || CC == ISD::SETGT || CC == ISD::SETULT)) ||
9163 (CRHS->isNullValue() &&
9164 (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETGE || CC == ISD::SETULE)))
9165 return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, SL, MVT::i1, LHS.getOperand(0),
9166 DAG.getConstant(-1, SL, MVT::i1));
9167 if ((CRHS->isAllOnesValue() &&
9168 (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETLE || CC == ISD::SETUGE)) ||
9169 (CRHS->isNullValue() &&
9170 (CC == ISD::SETNE || CC == ISD::SETUGT || CC == ISD::SETLT)))
9171 return LHS.getOperand(0);
9172 }
9173
9174 uint64_t CRHSVal = CRHS->getZExtValue();
9175 if ((CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETNE) &&
9176 LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT &&
9177 isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(1)) &&
9178 isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2)) &&
9179 LHS.getConstantOperandVal(1) != LHS.getConstantOperandVal(2) &&
9180 isBoolSGPR(LHS.getOperand(0))) {
9181 // Given CT != FT:
9182 // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CF, eq => xor cc, -1
9183 // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CF, ne => cc
9184 // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CT, ne => xor cc, -1
9185 // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CT, eq => cc
9186 uint64_t CT = LHS.getConstantOperandVal(1);
9187 uint64_t CF = LHS.getConstantOperandVal(2);
9188
9189 if ((CF == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETEQ) ||
9190 (CT == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETNE))
9191 return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, SL, MVT::i1, LHS.getOperand(0),
9192 DAG.getConstant(-1, SL, MVT::i1));
9193 if ((CF == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETNE) ||
9194 (CT == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETEQ))
9195 return LHS.getOperand(0);
9196 }
9197 }
9198
9199 if (VT != MVT::f32 && VT != MVT::f64 && (Subtarget->has16BitInsts() &&
9200 VT != MVT::f16))
9201 return SDValue();
9202
9203 // Match isinf/isfinite pattern
9204 // (fcmp oeq (fabs x), inf) -> (fp_class x, (p_infinity | n_infinity))
9205 // (fcmp one (fabs x), inf) -> (fp_class x,
9206 // (p_normal | n_normal | p_subnormal | n_subnormal | p_zero | n_zero)
9207 if ((CC == ISD::SETOEQ || CC == ISD::SETONE) && LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) {
9208 const ConstantFPSDNode *CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(RHS);
9209 if (!CRHS)
9210 return SDValue();
9211
9212 const APFloat &APF = CRHS->getValueAPF();
9213 if (APF.isInfinity() && !APF.isNegative()) {
9214 const unsigned IsInfMask = SIInstrFlags::P_INFINITY |
9215 SIInstrFlags::N_INFINITY;
9216 const unsigned IsFiniteMask = SIInstrFlags::N_ZERO |
9217 SIInstrFlags::P_ZERO |
9218 SIInstrFlags::N_NORMAL |
9219 SIInstrFlags::P_NORMAL |
9220 SIInstrFlags::N_SUBNORMAL |
9221 SIInstrFlags::P_SUBNORMAL;
9222 unsigned Mask = CC == ISD::SETOEQ ? IsInfMask : IsFiniteMask;
9223 return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS, SL, MVT::i1, LHS.getOperand(0),
9224 DAG.getConstant(Mask, SL, MVT::i32));
9225 }
9226 }
9227
9228 return SDValue();
9229}
9230
9231SDValue SITargetLowering::performCvtF32UByteNCombine(SDNode *N,
9232 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9233 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9234 SDLoc SL(N);
9235 unsigned Offset = N->getOpcode() - AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0;
9236
9237 SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
9238 SDValue Srl = N->getOperand(0);
9239 if (Srl.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
9240 Srl = Srl.getOperand(0);
9241
9242 // TODO: Handle (or x, (srl y, 8)) pattern when known bits are zero.
9243 if (Srl.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) {
9244 // cvt_f32_ubyte0 (srl x, 16) -> cvt_f32_ubyte2 x
9245 // cvt_f32_ubyte1 (srl x, 16) -> cvt_f32_ubyte3 x
9246 // cvt_f32_ubyte0 (srl x, 8) -> cvt_f32_ubyte1 x
9247
9248 if (const ConstantSDNode *C =
9249 dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Srl.getOperand(1))) {
9250 Srl = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Srl.getOperand(0), SDLoc(Srl.getOperand(0)),
9251 EVT(MVT::i32));
9252
9253 unsigned SrcOffset = C->getZExtValue() + 8 * Offset;
9254 if (SrcOffset < 32 && SrcOffset % 8 == 0) {
9255 return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0 + SrcOffset / 8, SL,
9256 MVT::f32, Srl);
9257 }
9258 }
9259 }
9260
9261 APInt Demanded = APInt::getBitsSet(32, 8 * Offset, 8 * Offset + 8);
9262
9263 KnownBits Known;
9264 TargetLowering::TargetLoweringOpt TLO(DAG, !DCI.isBeforeLegalize(),
9265 !DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps());
9266 const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
9267 if (TLI.SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, Demanded, Known, TLO)) {
9268 DCI.CommitTargetLoweringOpt(TLO);
9269 }
9270
9271 return SDValue();
9272}
9273
9274SDValue SITargetLowering::performClampCombine(SDNode *N,
9275 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9276 ConstantFPSDNode *CSrc = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N->getOperand(0));
9277 if (!CSrc)
9278 return SDValue();
9279
9280 const MachineFunction &MF = DCI.DAG.getMachineFunction();
9281 const APFloat &F = CSrc->getValueAPF();
9282 APFloat Zero = APFloat::getZero(F.getSemantics());
9283 APFloat::cmpResult Cmp0 = F.compare(Zero);
9284 if (Cmp0 == APFloat::cmpLessThan ||
9285 (Cmp0 == APFloat::cmpUnordered &&
9286 MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>()->getMode().DX10Clamp)) {
9287 return DCI.DAG.getConstantFP(Zero, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0));
9288 }
9289
9290 APFloat One(F.getSemantics(), "1.0");
9291 APFloat::cmpResult Cmp1 = F.compare(One);
9292 if (Cmp1 == APFloat::cmpGreaterThan)
9293 return DCI.DAG.getConstantFP(One, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0));
9294
9295 return SDValue(CSrc, 0);
9296}
9297
9298
9299SDValue SITargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
9300 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9301 if (getTargetMachine().getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::None)
9302 return SDValue();
9303 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
9304 default:
9305 return AMDGPUTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(N, DCI);
9306 case ISD::ADD:
9307 return performAddCombine(N, DCI);
9308 case ISD::SUB:
9309 return performSubCombine(N, DCI);
9310 case ISD::ADDCARRY:
9311 case ISD::SUBCARRY:
9312 return performAddCarrySubCarryCombine(N, DCI);
9313 case ISD::FADD:
9314 return performFAddCombine(N, DCI);
9315 case ISD::FSUB:
9316 return performFSubCombine(N, DCI);
9317 case ISD::SETCC:
9318 return performSetCCCombine(N, DCI);
9319 case ISD::FMAXNUM:
9320 case ISD::FMINNUM:
9321 case ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE:
9322 case ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE:
9323 case ISD::SMAX:
9324 case ISD::SMIN:
9325 case ISD::UMAX:
9326 case ISD::UMIN:
9327 case AMDGPUISD::FMIN_LEGACY:
9328 case AMDGPUISD::FMAX_LEGACY:
9329 return performMinMaxCombine(N, DCI);
9330 case ISD::FMA:
9331 return performFMACombine(N, DCI);
9332 case ISD::LOAD: {
9333 if (SDValue Widended = widenLoad(cast<LoadSDNode>(N), DCI))
9334 return Widended;
9335 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
9336 }
9337 case ISD::STORE:
9338 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD:
9339 case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE:
9340 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP:
9341 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS:
9342 case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP:
9343 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD:
9344 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB:
9345 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND:
9346 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR:
9347 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR:
9348 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND:
9349 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN:
9350 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX:
9351 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN:
9352 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX:
9353 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FADD:
9354 case AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_INC:
9355 case AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_DEC:
9356 case AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMIN:
9357 case AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMAX: // TODO: Target mem intrinsics.
9358 if (DCI.isBeforeLegalize())
9359 break;
9360 return performMemSDNodeCombine(cast<MemSDNode>(N), DCI);
9361 case ISD::AND:
9362 return performAndCombine(N, DCI);
9363 case ISD::OR:
9364 return performOrCombine(N, DCI);
9365 case ISD::XOR:
9366 return performXorCombine(N, DCI);
9367 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
9368 return performZeroExtendCombine(N, DCI);
9369 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
9370 return performSignExtendInRegCombine(N , DCI);
9371 case AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS:
9372 return performClassCombine(N, DCI);
9373 case ISD::FCANONICALIZE:
9374 return performFCanonicalizeCombine(N, DCI);
9375 case AMDGPUISD::RCP:
9376 return performRcpCombine(N, DCI);
9377 case AMDGPUISD::FRACT:
9378 case AMDGPUISD::RSQ:
9379 case AMDGPUISD::RCP_LEGACY:
9380 case AMDGPUISD::RSQ_LEGACY:
9381 case AMDGPUISD::RCP_IFLAG:
9382 case AMDGPUISD::RSQ_CLAMP:
9383 case AMDGPUISD::LDEXP: {
9384 SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
9385 if (Src.isUndef())
9386 return Src;
9387 break;
9388 }
9389 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
9390 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
9391 return performUCharToFloatCombine(N, DCI);
9392 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0:
9393 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE1:
9394 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE2:
9395 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE3:
9396 return performCvtF32UByteNCombine(N, DCI);
9397 case AMDGPUISD::FMED3:
9398 return performFMed3Combine(N, DCI);
9399 case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKRTZ_F16_F32:
9400 return performCvtPkRTZCombine(N, DCI);
9401 case AMDGPUISD::CLAMP:
9402 return performClampCombine(N, DCI);
9403 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: {
9404 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9405 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9406
9407 // v2i16 (scalar_to_vector i16:x) -> v2i16 (bitcast (any_extend i16:x))
9408 if (VT == MVT::v2i16 || VT == MVT::v2f16) {
9409 SDLoc SL(N);
9410 SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
9411 EVT EltVT = Src.getValueType();
9412 if (EltVT == MVT::f16)
9413 Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i16, Src);
9414
9415 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i32, Src);
9416 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, Ext);
9417 }
9418
9419 break;
9420 }
9421 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
9422 return performExtractVectorEltCombine(N, DCI);
9423 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT:
9424 return performInsertVectorEltCombine(N, DCI);
9425 }
9426 return AMDGPUTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(N, DCI);
9427}
9428
9429/// Helper function for adjustWritemask
9430static unsigned SubIdx2Lane(unsigned Idx) {
9431 switch (Idx) {
9432 default: return 0;
9433 case AMDGPU::sub0: return 0;
9434 case AMDGPU::sub1: return 1;
9435 case AMDGPU::sub2: return 2;
9436 case AMDGPU::sub3: return 3;
9437 case AMDGPU::sub4: return 4; // Possible with TFE/LWE
9438 }
9439}
9440
9441/// Adjust the writemask of MIMG instructions
9442SDNode *SITargetLowering::adjustWritemask(MachineSDNode *&Node,
9443 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9444 unsigned Opcode = Node->getMachineOpcode();
9445
9446 // Subtract 1 because the vdata output is not a MachineSDNode operand.
9447 int D16Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::d16) - 1;
9448 if (D16Idx >= 0 && Node->getConstantOperandVal(D16Idx))
9449 return Node; // not implemented for D16
9450
9451 SDNode *Users[5] = { nullptr };
9452 unsigned Lane = 0;
9453 unsigned DmaskIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask) - 1;
9454 unsigned OldDmask = Node->getConstantOperandVal(DmaskIdx);
9455 unsigned NewDmask = 0;
9456 unsigned TFEIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::tfe) - 1;
9457 unsigned LWEIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::lwe) - 1;
9458 bool UsesTFC = (Node->getConstantOperandVal(TFEIdx) ||
9459 Node->getConstantOperandVal(LWEIdx)) ? 1 : 0;
9460 unsigned TFCLane = 0;
9461 bool HasChain = Node->getNumValues() > 1;
9462
9463 if (OldDmask == 0) {
9464 // These are folded out, but on the chance it happens don't assert.
9465 return Node;
9466 }
9467
9468 unsigned OldBitsSet = countPopulation(OldDmask);
9469 // Work out which is the TFE/LWE lane if that is enabled.
9470 if (UsesTFC) {
9471 TFCLane = OldBitsSet;
9472 }
9473
9474 // Try to figure out the used register components
9475 for (SDNode::use_iterator I = Node->use_begin(), E = Node->use_end();
9476 I != E; ++I) {
9477
9478 // Don't look at users of the chain.
9479 if (I.getUse().getResNo() != 0)
9480 continue;
9481
9482 // Abort if we can't understand the usage
9483 if (!I->isMachineOpcode() ||
9484 I->getMachineOpcode() != TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG)
9485 return Node;
9486
9487 // Lane means which subreg of %vgpra_vgprb_vgprc_vgprd is used.
9488 // Note that subregs are packed, i.e. Lane==0 is the first bit set
9489 // in OldDmask, so it can be any of X,Y,Z,W; Lane==1 is the second bit
9490 // set, etc.
9491 Lane = SubIdx2Lane(I->getConstantOperandVal(1));
9492
9493 // Check if the use is for the TFE/LWE generated result at VGPRn+1.
9494 if (UsesTFC && Lane == TFCLane) {
9495 Users[Lane] = *I;
9496 } else {
9497 // Set which texture component corresponds to the lane.
9498 unsigned Comp;
9499 for (unsigned i = 0, Dmask = OldDmask; (i <= Lane) && (Dmask != 0); i++) {
9500 Comp = countTrailingZeros(Dmask);
9501 Dmask &= ~(1 << Comp);
9502 }
9503
9504 // Abort if we have more than one user per component.
9505 if (Users[Lane])
9506 return Node;
9507
9508 Users[Lane] = *I;
9509 NewDmask |= 1 << Comp;
9510 }
9511 }
9512
9513 // Don't allow 0 dmask, as hardware assumes one channel enabled.
9514 bool NoChannels = !NewDmask;
9515 if (NoChannels) {
9516 if (!UsesTFC) {
9517 // No uses of the result and not using TFC. Then do nothing.
9518 return Node;
9519 }
9520 // If the original dmask has one channel - then nothing to do
9521 if (OldBitsSet == 1)
9522 return Node;
9523 // Use an arbitrary dmask - required for the instruction to work
9524 NewDmask = 1;
9525 }
9526 // Abort if there's no change
9527 if (NewDmask == OldDmask)
9528 return Node;
9529
9530 unsigned BitsSet = countPopulation(NewDmask);
9531
9532 // Check for TFE or LWE - increase the number of channels by one to account
9533 // for the extra return value
9534 // This will need adjustment for D16 if this is also included in
9535 // adjustWriteMask (this function) but at present D16 are excluded.
9536 unsigned NewChannels = BitsSet + UsesTFC;
9537
9538 int NewOpcode =
9539 AMDGPU::getMaskedMIMGOp(Node->getMachineOpcode(), NewChannels);
9540 assert(NewOpcode != -1 &&
9541 NewOpcode != static_cast<int>(Node->getMachineOpcode()) &&
9542 "failed to find equivalent MIMG op");
9543
9544 // Adjust the writemask in the node
9545 SmallVector<SDValue, 12> Ops;
9546 Ops.insert(Ops.end(), Node->op_begin(), Node->op_begin() + DmaskIdx);
9547 Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(NewDmask, SDLoc(Node), MVT::i32));
9548 Ops.insert(Ops.end(), Node->op_begin() + DmaskIdx + 1, Node->op_end());
9549
9550 MVT SVT = Node->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType().getSimpleVT();
9551
9552 MVT ResultVT = NewChannels == 1 ?
9553 SVT : MVT::getVectorVT(SVT, NewChannels == 3 ? 4 :
9554 NewChannels == 5 ? 8 : NewChannels);
9555 SDVTList NewVTList = HasChain ?
9556 DAG.getVTList(ResultVT, MVT::Other) : DAG.getVTList(ResultVT);
9557
9558
9559 MachineSDNode *NewNode = DAG.getMachineNode(NewOpcode, SDLoc(Node),
9560 NewVTList, Ops);
9561
9562 if (HasChain) {
9563 // Update chain.
9564 DAG.setNodeMemRefs(NewNode, Node->memoperands());
9565 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 1), SDValue(NewNode, 1));
9566 }
9567
9568 if (NewChannels == 1) {
9569 assert(Node->hasNUsesOfValue(1, 0));
9570 SDNode *Copy = DAG.getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY,
9571 SDLoc(Node), Users[Lane]->getValueType(0),
9572 SDValue(NewNode, 0));
9573 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Users[Lane], Copy);
9574 return nullptr;
9575 }
9576
9577 // Update the users of the node with the new indices
9578 for (unsigned i = 0, Idx = AMDGPU::sub0; i < 5; ++i) {
9579 SDNode *User = Users[i];
9580 if (!User) {
9581 // Handle the special case of NoChannels. We set NewDmask to 1 above, but
9582 // Users[0] is still nullptr because channel 0 doesn't really have a use.
9583 if (i || !NoChannels)
9584 continue;
9585 } else {
9586 SDValue Op = DAG.getTargetConstant(Idx, SDLoc(User), MVT::i32);
9587 DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(User, SDValue(NewNode, 0), Op);
9588 }
9589
9590 switch (Idx) {
9591 default: break;
9592 case AMDGPU::sub0: Idx = AMDGPU::sub1; break;
9593 case AMDGPU::sub1: Idx = AMDGPU::sub2; break;
9594 case AMDGPU::sub2: Idx = AMDGPU::sub3; break;
9595 case AMDGPU::sub3: Idx = AMDGPU::sub4; break;
9596 }
9597 }
9598
9599 DAG.RemoveDeadNode(Node);
9600 return nullptr;
9601}
9602
9603static bool isFrameIndexOp(SDValue Op) {
9604 if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::AssertZext)
9605 Op = Op.getOperand(0);
9606
9607 return isa<FrameIndexSDNode>(Op);
9608}
9609
9610/// Legalize target independent instructions (e.g. INSERT_SUBREG)
9611/// with frame index operands.
9612/// LLVM assumes that inputs are to these instructions are registers.
9613SDNode *SITargetLowering::legalizeTargetIndependentNode(SDNode *Node,
9614 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9615 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyToReg) {
9616 RegisterSDNode *DestReg = cast<RegisterSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1));
9617 SDValue SrcVal = Node->getOperand(2);
9618
9619 // Insert a copy to a VReg_1 virtual register so LowerI1Copies doesn't have
9620 // to try understanding copies to physical registers.
9621 if (SrcVal.getValueType() == MVT::i1 &&
9622 TargetRegisterInfo::isPhysicalRegister(DestReg->getReg())) {
9623 SDLoc SL(Node);
9624 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getRegInfo();
9625 SDValue VReg = DAG.getRegister(
9626 MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VReg_1RegClass), MVT::i1);
9627
9628 SDNode *Glued = Node->getGluedNode();
9629 SDValue ToVReg
9630 = DAG.getCopyToReg(Node->getOperand(0), SL, VReg, SrcVal,
9631 SDValue(Glued, Glued ? Glued->getNumValues() - 1 : 0));
9632 SDValue ToResultReg
9633 = DAG.getCopyToReg(ToVReg, SL, SDValue(DestReg, 0),
9634 VReg, ToVReg.getValue(1));
9635 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Node, ToResultReg.getNode());
9636 DAG.RemoveDeadNode(Node);
9637 return ToResultReg.getNode();
9638 }
9639 }
9640
9641 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
9642 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Node->getNumOperands(); ++i) {
9643 if (!isFrameIndexOp(Node->getOperand(i))) {
9644 Ops.push_back(Node->getOperand(i));
9645 continue;
9646 }
9647
9648 SDLoc DL(Node);
9649 Ops.push_back(SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL,
9650 Node->getOperand(i).getValueType(),
9651 Node->getOperand(i)), 0));
9652 }
9653
9654 return DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(Node, Ops);
9655}
9656
9657/// Fold the instructions after selecting them.
9658/// Returns null if users were already updated.
9659SDNode *SITargetLowering::PostISelFolding(MachineSDNode *Node,
9660 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9661 const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
9662 unsigned Opcode = Node->getMachineOpcode();
9663
9664 if (TII->isMIMG(Opcode) && !TII->get(Opcode).mayStore() &&
9665 !TII->isGather4(Opcode)) {
9666 return adjustWritemask(Node, DAG);
9667 }
9668
9669 if (Opcode == AMDGPU::INSERT_SUBREG ||
9670 Opcode == AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE) {
9671 legalizeTargetIndependentNode(Node, DAG);
9672 return Node;
9673 }
9674
9675 switch (Opcode) {
9676 case AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F32:
9677 case AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F64: {
9678 // Satisfy the operand register constraint when one of the inputs is
9679 // undefined. Ordinarily each undef value will have its own implicit_def of
9680 // a vreg, so force these to use a single register.
9681 SDValue Src0 = Node->getOperand(0);
9682 SDValue Src1 = Node->getOperand(1);
9683 SDValue Src2 = Node->getOperand(2);
9684
9685 if ((Src0.isMachineOpcode() &&
9686 Src0.getMachineOpcode() != AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF) &&
9687 (Src0 == Src1 || Src0 == Src2))
9688 break;
9689
9690 MVT VT = Src0.getValueType().getSimpleVT();
9691 const TargetRegisterClass *RC =
9692 getRegClassFor(VT, Src0.getNode()->isDivergent());
9693
9694 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getRegInfo();
9695 SDValue UndefReg = DAG.getRegister(MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC), VT);
9696
9697 SDValue ImpDef = DAG.getCopyToReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), SDLoc(Node),
9698 UndefReg, Src0, SDValue());
9699
9700 // src0 must be the same register as src1 or src2, even if the value is
9701 // undefined, so make sure we don't violate this constraint.
9702 if (Src0.isMachineOpcode() &&
9703 Src0.getMachineOpcode() == AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF) {
9704 if (Src1.isMachineOpcode() &&
9705 Src1.getMachineOpcode() != AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF)
9706 Src0 = Src1;
9707 else if (Src2.isMachineOpcode() &&
9708 Src2.getMachineOpcode() != AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF)
9709 Src0 = Src2;
9710 else {
9711 assert(Src1.getMachineOpcode() == AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF);
9712 Src0 = UndefReg;
9713 Src1 = UndefReg;
9714 }
9715 } else
9716 break;
9717
9718 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops = { Src0, Src1, Src2 };
9719 for (unsigned I = 3, N = Node->getNumOperands(); I != N; ++I)
9720 Ops.push_back(Node->getOperand(I));
9721
9722 Ops.push_back(ImpDef.getValue(1));
9723 return DAG.getMachineNode(Opcode, SDLoc(Node), Node->getVTList(), Ops);
9724 }
9725 case AMDGPU::V_PERMLANE16_B32:
9726 case AMDGPU::V_PERMLANEX16_B32: {
9727 ConstantSDNode *FI = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node->getOperand(0));
9728 ConstantSDNode *BC = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node->getOperand(2));
9729 if (!FI->getZExtValue() && !BC->getZExtValue())
9730 break;
9731 SDValue VDstIn = Node->getOperand(6);
9732 if (VDstIn.isMachineOpcode()
9733 && VDstIn.getMachineOpcode() == AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF)
9734 break;
9735 MachineSDNode *ImpDef = DAG.getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF,
9736 SDLoc(Node), MVT::i32);
9737 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops = { SDValue(FI, 0), Node->getOperand(1),
9738 SDValue(BC, 0), Node->getOperand(3),
9739 Node->getOperand(4), Node->getOperand(5),
9740 SDValue(ImpDef, 0), Node->getOperand(7) };
9741 return DAG.getMachineNode(Opcode, SDLoc(Node), Node->getVTList(), Ops);
9742 }
9743 default:
9744 break;
9745 }
9746
9747 return Node;
9748}
9749
9750/// Assign the register class depending on the number of
9751/// bits set in the writemask
9752void SITargetLowering::AdjustInstrPostInstrSelection(MachineInstr &MI,
9753 SDNode *Node) const {
9754 const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
9755
9756 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MI.getParent()->getParent()->getRegInfo();
9757
9758 if (TII->isVOP3(MI.getOpcode())) {
9759 // Make sure constant bus requirements are respected.
9760 TII->legalizeOperandsVOP3(MRI, MI);
9761 return;
9762 }
9763
9764 // Replace unused atomics with the no return version.
9765 int NoRetAtomicOp = AMDGPU::getAtomicNoRetOp(MI.getOpcode());
9766 if (NoRetAtomicOp != -1) {
9767 if (!Node->hasAnyUseOfValue(0)) {
9768 MI.setDesc(TII->get(NoRetAtomicOp));
9769 MI.RemoveOperand(0);
9770 return;
9771 }
9772
9773 // For mubuf_atomic_cmpswap, we need to have tablegen use an extract_subreg
9774 // instruction, because the return type of these instructions is a vec2 of
9775 // the memory type, so it can be tied to the input operand.
9776 // This means these instructions always have a use, so we need to add a
9777 // special case to check if the atomic has only one extract_subreg use,
9778 // which itself has no uses.
9779 if ((Node->hasNUsesOfValue(1, 0) &&
9780 Node->use_begin()->isMachineOpcode() &&
9781 Node->use_begin()->getMachineOpcode() == AMDGPU::EXTRACT_SUBREG &&
9782 !Node->use_begin()->hasAnyUseOfValue(0))) {
9783 unsigned Def = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
9784
9785 // Change this into a noret atomic.
9786 MI.setDesc(TII->get(NoRetAtomicOp));
9787 MI.RemoveOperand(0);
9788
9789 // If we only remove the def operand from the atomic instruction, the
9790 // extract_subreg will be left with a use of a vreg without a def.
9791 // So we need to insert an implicit_def to avoid machine verifier
9792 // errors.
9793 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI, MI.getDebugLoc(),
9794 TII->get(AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF), Def);
9795 }
9796 return;
9797 }
9798}
9799
9800static SDValue buildSMovImm32(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL,
9801 uint64_t Val) {
9802 SDValue K = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, MVT::i32);
9803 return SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL, MVT::i32, K), 0);
9804}
9805
9806MachineSDNode *SITargetLowering::wrapAddr64Rsrc(SelectionDAG &DAG,
9807 const SDLoc &DL,
9808 SDValue Ptr) const {
9809 const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
9810
9811 // Build the half of the subregister with the constants before building the
9812 // full 128-bit register. If we are building multiple resource descriptors,
9813 // this will allow CSEing of the 2-component register.
9814 const SDValue Ops0[] = {
9815 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SGPR_64RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32),
9816 buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL, 0),
9817 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32),
9818 buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL, TII->getDefaultRsrcDataFormat() >> 32),
9819 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32)
9820 };
9821
9822 SDValue SubRegHi = SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL,
9823 MVT::v2i32, Ops0), 0);
9824
9825 // Combine the constants and the pointer.
9826 const SDValue Ops1[] = {
9827 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SReg_128RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32),
9828 Ptr,
9829 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0_sub1, DL, MVT::i32),
9830 SubRegHi,
9831 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub2_sub3, DL, MVT::i32)
9832 };
9833
9834 return DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, MVT::v4i32, Ops1);
9835}
9836
9837/// Return a resource descriptor with the 'Add TID' bit enabled
9838/// The TID (Thread ID) is multiplied by the stride value (bits [61:48]
9839/// of the resource descriptor) to create an offset, which is added to
9840/// the resource pointer.
9841MachineSDNode *SITargetLowering::buildRSRC(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL,
9842 SDValue Ptr, uint32_t RsrcDword1,
9843 uint64_t RsrcDword2And3) const {
9844 SDValue PtrLo = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32, Ptr);
9845 SDValue PtrHi = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32, Ptr);
9846 if (RsrcDword1) {
9847 PtrHi = SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_OR_B32, DL, MVT::i32, PtrHi,
9848 DAG.getConstant(RsrcDword1, DL, MVT::i32)),
9849 0);
9850 }
9851
9852 SDValue DataLo = buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL,
9853 RsrcDword2And3 & UINT64_C(0xFFFFFFFF));
9854 SDValue DataHi = buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL, RsrcDword2And3 >> 32);
9855
9856 const SDValue Ops[] = {
9857 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SReg_128RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32),
9858 PtrLo,
9859 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32),
9860 PtrHi,
9861 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32),
9862 DataLo,
9863 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub2, DL, MVT::i32),
9864 DataHi,
9865 DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub3, DL, MVT::i32)
9866 };
9867
9868 return DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, MVT::v4i32, Ops);
9869}

9871//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9872// SI Inline Assembly Support
9873//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9874
9875std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *>
9876SITargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
9877 StringRef Constraint,
9878 MVT VT) const {
9879 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = nullptr;
9880 if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
9881 switch (Constraint[0]) {
9882 default:
9883 return TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
9884 case 's':
9885 case 'r':
9886 switch (VT.getSizeInBits()) {
9887 default:
9888 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
9889 case 32:
9890 case 16:
9891 RC = &AMDGPU::SReg_32_XM0RegClass;
9892 break;
9893 case 64:
9894 RC = &AMDGPU::SGPR_64RegClass;
9895 break;
9896 case 96:
9897 RC = &AMDGPU::SReg_96RegClass;
9898 break;
9899 case 128:
9900 RC = &AMDGPU::SReg_128RegClass;
9901 break;
9902 case 160:
9903 RC = &AMDGPU::SReg_160RegClass;
9904 break;
9905 case 256:
9906 RC = &AMDGPU::SReg_256RegClass;
9907 break;
9908 case 512:
9909 RC = &AMDGPU::SReg_512RegClass;
9910 break;
9911 }
9912 break;
9913 case 'v':
9914 switch (VT.getSizeInBits()) {
9915 default:
9916 return std::make_pair(0U, nullptr);
9917 case 32:
9918 case 16:
9919 RC = &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass;
9920 break;
9921 case 64:
9922 RC = &AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClass;
9923 break;
9924 case 96:
9925 RC = &AMDGPU::VReg_96RegClass;
9926 break;
9927 case 128:
9928 RC = &AMDGPU::VReg_128RegClass;
9929 break;
9930 case 160:
9931 RC = &AMDGPU::VReg_160RegClass;
9932 break;
9933 case 256:
9934 RC = &AMDGPU::VReg_256RegClass;
9935 break;
9936 case 512:
9937 RC = &AMDGPU::VReg_512RegClass;
9938 break;
9939 }
9940 break;
9941 }
9942 // We actually support i128, i16 and f16 as inline parameters
9943 // even if they are not reported as legal
9944 if (RC && (isTypeLegal(VT) || VT.SimpleTy == MVT::i128 ||
9945 VT.SimpleTy == MVT::i16 || VT.SimpleTy == MVT::f16))
9946 return std::make_pair(0U, RC);
9947 }
9948
9949 if (Constraint.size() > 1) {
9950 if (Constraint[1] == 'v') {
9951 RC = &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass;
9952 } else if (Constraint[1] == 's') {
9953 RC = &AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass;
9954 }
9955
9956 if (RC) {
9957 uint32_t Idx;
9958 bool Failed = Constraint.substr(2).getAsInteger(10, Idx);
9959 if (!Failed && Idx < RC->getNumRegs())
9960 return std::make_pair(RC->getRegister(Idx), RC);
9961 }
9962 }
9963 return TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
9964}
9965
9966SITargetLowering::ConstraintType
9967SITargetLowering::getConstraintType(StringRef Constraint) const {
9968 if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
9969 switch (Constraint[0]) {
9970 default: break;
9971 case 's':
9972 case 'v':
9973 return C_RegisterClass;
9974 }
9975 }
9976 return TargetLowering::getConstraintType(Constraint);
9977}
9978
9979// Figure out which registers should be reserved for stack access. Only after
9980// the function is legalized do we know all of the non-spill stack objects or if
9981// calls are present.
9982void SITargetLowering::finalizeLowering(MachineFunction &MF) const {
9983 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
9984 SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
9985 const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
9986
9987 if (Info->isEntryFunction()) {
9988 // Callable functions have fixed registers used for stack access.
9989 reservePrivateMemoryRegs(getTargetMachine(), MF, *TRI, *Info);
9990 }
9991
9992 assert(!TRI->isSubRegister(Info->getScratchRSrcReg(),
9993 Info->getStackPtrOffsetReg()));
9994 if (Info->getStackPtrOffsetReg() != AMDGPU::SP_REG)
9995 MRI.replaceRegWith(AMDGPU::SP_REG, Info->getStackPtrOffsetReg());
9996
9997 // We need to worry about replacing the default register with itself in case
9998 // of MIR testcases missing the MFI.
9999 if (Info->getScratchRSrcReg() != AMDGPU::PRIVATE_RSRC_REG)
10000 MRI.replaceRegWith(AMDGPU::PRIVATE_RSRC_REG, Info->getScratchRSrcReg());
10001
10002 if (Info->getFrameOffsetReg() != AMDGPU::FP_REG)
10003 MRI.replaceRegWith(AMDGPU::FP_REG, Info->getFrameOffsetReg());
10004
10005 if (Info->getScratchWaveOffsetReg() != AMDGPU::SCRATCH_WAVE_OFFSET_REG) {
10006 MRI.replaceRegWith(AMDGPU::SCRATCH_WAVE_OFFSET_REG,
10007 Info->getScratchWaveOffsetReg());
10008 }
10009
10010 Info->limitOccupancy(MF);
10011
10012 TargetLoweringBase::finalizeLowering(MF);
10013}
10014
10015void SITargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForFrameIndex(const SDValue Op,
10016 KnownBits &Known,
10017 const APInt &DemandedElts,
10018 const SelectionDAG &DAG,
10019 unsigned Depth) const {
10020 TargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForFrameIndex(Op, Known, DemandedElts,
10021 DAG, Depth);
10022
10023 // Set the high bits to zero based on the maximum allowed scratch size per
10024 // wave. We can't use vaddr in MUBUF instructions if we don't know the address
10025 // calculation won't overflow, so assume the sign bit is never set.
10026 Known.Zero.setHighBits(getSubtarget()->getKnownHighZeroBitsForFrameIndex());
10027}
10028
10029unsigned SITargetLowering::getPrefLoopAlignment(MachineLoop *ML) const {
10030 const unsigned PrefAlign = TargetLowering::getPrefLoopAlignment(ML);
10031 const unsigned CacheLineAlign = 6; // log2(64)
10032
10033 // Pre-GFX10 target did not benefit from loop alignment
10034 if (!ML || DisableLoopAlignment ||
10035 (getSubtarget()->getGeneration() < AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10) ||
10036 getSubtarget()->hasInstFwdPrefetchBug())
10037 return PrefAlign;
10038
10039 // On GFX10 I$ is 4 x 64 bytes cache lines.
10040 // By default prefetcher keeps one cache line behind and reads two ahead.
10041 // We can modify it with S_INST_PREFETCH for larger loops to have two lines
10042 // behind and one ahead.
10043 // Therefor we can benefit from aligning loop headers if loop fits 192 bytes.
10044 // If loop fits 64 bytes it always spans no more than two cache lines and
10045 // does not need an alignment.
10046 // Else if loop is less or equal 128 bytes we do not need to modify prefetch,
10047 // Else if loop is less or equal 192 bytes we need two lines behind.
10048
10049 const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
10050 const MachineBasicBlock *Header = ML->getHeader();
10051 if (Header->getAlignment() != PrefAlign)
10052 return Header->getAlignment(); // Already processed.
10053
10054 unsigned LoopSize = 0;
10055 for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : ML->blocks()) {
10056 // If inner loop block is aligned assume in average half of the alignment
10057 // size to be added as nops.
10058 if (MBB != Header)
10059 LoopSize += (1 << MBB->getAlignment()) / 2;
10060
10061 for (const MachineInstr &MI : *MBB) {
10062 LoopSize += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MI);
10063 if (LoopSize > 192)
10064 return PrefAlign;
10065 }
10066 }
10067
10068 if (LoopSize <= 64)
10069 return PrefAlign;
10070
10071 if (LoopSize <= 128)
10072 return CacheLineAlign;
10073
10074 // If any of parent loops is surrounded by prefetch instructions do not
10075 // insert new for inner loop, which would reset parent's settings.
10076 for (MachineLoop *P = ML->getParentLoop(); P; P = P->getParentLoop()) {
10077 if (MachineBasicBlock *Exit = P->getExitBlock()) {
10078 auto I = Exit->getFirstNonDebugInstr();
10079 if (I != Exit->end() && I->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH)
10080 return CacheLineAlign;
10081 }
10082 }
10083
10084 MachineBasicBlock *Pre = ML->getLoopPreheader();
10085 MachineBasicBlock *Exit = ML->getExitBlock();
10086
10087 if (Pre && Exit) {
10088 BuildMI(*Pre, Pre->getFirstTerminator(), DebugLoc(),
10089 TII->get(AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH))
10090 .addImm(1); // prefetch 2 lines behind PC
10091
10092 BuildMI(*Exit, Exit->getFirstNonDebugInstr(), DebugLoc(),
10093 TII->get(AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH))
10094 .addImm(2); // prefetch 1 line behind PC
10095 }
10096
10097 return CacheLineAlign;
10098}
10099
10100LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED
10101static bool isCopyFromRegOfInlineAsm(const SDNode *N) {
10102 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyFromReg);
10103 do {
10104 // Follow the chain until we find an INLINEASM node.
10105 N = N->getOperand(0).getNode();
10106 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::INLINEASM ||
10107 N->getOpcode() == ISD::INLINEASM_BR)
10108 return true;
10109 } while (N->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyFromReg);
10110 return false;
10111}
10112
10113bool SITargetLowering::isSDNodeSourceOfDivergence(const SDNode * N,
10114 FunctionLoweringInfo * FLI, LegacyDivergenceAnalysis * KDA) const
10115{
10116 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
10117 case ISD::CopyFromReg:
10118 {
10119 const RegisterSDNode *R = cast<RegisterSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
10120 const MachineFunction * MF = FLI->MF;
10121 const GCNSubtarget &ST = MF->getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>();
10122 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo();
10123 const SIRegisterInfo &TRI = ST.getInstrInfo()->getRegisterInfo();
10124 unsigned Reg = R->getReg();
10125 if (TRI.isPhysicalRegister(Reg))
10126 return !TRI.isSGPRReg(MRI, Reg);
10127
10128 if (MRI.isLiveIn(Reg)) {
10129 // workitem.id.x workitem.id.y workitem.id.z
10130 // Any VGPR formal argument is also considered divergent
10131 if (!TRI.isSGPRReg(MRI, Reg))
10132 return true;
10133 // Formal arguments of non-entry functions
10134 // are conservatively considered divergent
10135 else if (!AMDGPU::isEntryFunctionCC(FLI->Fn->getCallingConv()))
10136 return true;
10137 return false;
10138 }
10139 const Value *V = FLI->getValueFromVirtualReg(Reg);
10140 if (V)
10141 return KDA->isDivergent(V);
10142 assert(Reg == FLI->DemoteRegister || isCopyFromRegOfInlineAsm(N));
10143 return !TRI.isSGPRReg(MRI, Reg);
10144 }
10145 break;
10146 case ISD::LOAD: {
10147 const LoadSDNode *L = cast<LoadSDNode>(N);
10148 unsigned AS = L->getAddressSpace();
10149 // A flat load may access private memory.
10150 return AS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS || AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS;
10151 } break;
10152 case ISD::CALLSEQ_END:
10153 return true;
10154 break;
10155 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
10156 {
10157
10158 }
10159 return AMDGPU::isIntrinsicSourceOfDivergence(
10160 cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue());
10161 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
10162 return AMDGPU::isIntrinsicSourceOfDivergence(
10163 cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue());
10164 // In some cases intrinsics that are a source of divergence have been
10165 // lowered to AMDGPUISD so we also need to check those too.
10166 case AMDGPUISD::INTERP_MOV:
10167 case AMDGPUISD::INTERP_P1:
10168 case AMDGPUISD::INTERP_P2:
10169 return true;
10170 }
10171 return false;
10172}
10173
10174bool SITargetLowering::denormalsEnabledForType(EVT VT) const {
10175 switch (VT.getScalarType().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) {
10176 case MVT::f32:
10177 return Subtarget->hasFP32Denormals();
10178 case MVT::f64:
10179 return Subtarget->hasFP64Denormals();
10180 case MVT::f16:
10181 return Subtarget->hasFP16Denormals();
10182 default:
10183 return false;
10184 }
10185}
10186
10187bool SITargetLowering::isKnownNeverNaNForTargetNode(SDValue Op,
10188 const SelectionDAG &DAG,
10189 bool SNaN,
10190 unsigned Depth) const {
10191 if (Op.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::CLAMP) {
10192 const MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
10193 const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
10194
10195 if (Info->getMode().DX10Clamp)
10196 return true; // Clamped to 0.
10197 return DAG.isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1);
10198 }
10199
10200 return AMDGPUTargetLowering::isKnownNeverNaNForTargetNode(Op, DAG,
10201 SNaN, Depth);
10202}
10203
10204TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind
10205SITargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR(AtomicRMWInst *RMW) const {
10206 switch (RMW->getOperation()) {
10207 case AtomicRMWInst::FAdd: {
10208 Type *Ty = RMW->getType();
10209
10210 // We don't have a way to support 16-bit atomics now, so just leave them
10211 // as-is.
10212 if (Ty->isHalfTy())
10213 return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
10214
10215 if (!Ty->isFloatTy())
10216 return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
10217
10218 // TODO: Do have these for flat. Older targets also had them for buffers.
10219 unsigned AS = RMW->getPointerAddressSpace();
10220 return (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS && Subtarget->hasLDSFPAtomics()) ?
10221 AtomicExpansionKind::None : AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
10222 }
10223 default:
10224 break;
10225 }
10226
10227 return AMDGPUTargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR(RMW);
10228}
